1. Feature Name
Structure Selector
2. Goal
Enable users to select and apply proven narrative structures to their stories, choosing between deep guidance (5 curated structures with detailed beat-by-beat breakdowns) and light guidance (15+ structures with AI-generated outlines). This feature helps users organize their narrative with professional frameworks, ensuring proper pacing, emotional arcs, and satisfying story progression.
3. User Story
As a user developing my story,
I want to select a narrative structure that fits my story type and provides the right level of guidance,
So that I have a clear roadmap for organizing my narrative with proper pacing, emotional flow, and dramatic tension.
4. Functional Requirements
4.1 Core Functionality
4.1.1 Mode-Specific Behavior
Quick Mode (15-20 min):

AI automatically recommends 1 structure based on story type
Shows 3 pre-selected structure options
Brief overview only (no deep guidance)
AI generates simple beat-by-beat outline
User can accept AI suggestion or choose from 3 options

Comprehensive Mode (45-60 min):

User chooses guidance level first:

Deep Guidance: 5 structures with detailed step-by-step implementation
Light Guidance: 15+ structures with AI-generated outlines


Full structure exploration with examples, diagrams, and questions
Beat-by-beat editor with detailed prompts
Visual arc diagrams
Pacing calculator (for applicable structures)

4.1.2 Guidance Level Selection (Comprehensive Mode Only)
How much structure guidance do you want?
