7. AI Integration Specifications
7.1 AI Structure Recommendation
System Prompt:
javascriptconst structureRecommendationPrompt = `You are an expert in narrative structures and the Storyteller Tactics framework. Your task is to recommend the most appropriate story structure based on the user's context.

Consider:
- Story type and typical structures that work well for it
- Time constraints (quick vs. extended development)
- Audience expectations
- Character archetype and natural story arcs
- Complexity tolerance

Available structures:
${structures.map(s => `${s.name}: ${s.shortDesc} - Best for: ${s.bestFor.join(', ')}`).join('\n')}

Respond with JSON:
{
  "primary": {
    "structureId": "id",
    "confidence": "high" | "medium" | "low",
    "reasoning": "2-3 sentence explanation"
  },
  "alternatives": [
    {
      "structureId": "id",
      "reason": "Why this could also work"
    }
  ]
}`;
API Call:
javascriptconst recommendStructure = async (storyContext, availableStructures) => {
  const userPrompt = `Recommend the best narrative structure for this story:

Story Type: ${storyContext.storyType.type.name}
Category: ${storyContext.storyType.category}
Audience: ${storyContext.audience.primary}
Character: ${storyContext.character.primary?.name || 'Not selected'}
Mode: ${storyContext.mode} (${storyContext.mode === 'quick' ? 'needs quick structure' : 'can handle complex structure'})
Purpose: ${storyContext.purpose}

Which structure would work best?`;

  const response = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514',
      max_tokens: 1000,
      system: structureRecommendationPrompt,
      messages: [{ role: 'user', content: userPrompt }]
    })
  });

  const data = await response.json();
  const textContent = data.content.find(c => c.type === 'text')?.text || '{}';
  const cleaned = textContent.replace(/```json\n?|```\n?/g, '').trim();
  return JSON.parse(cleaned);
};
7.2 AI Beat Draft Generation (Deep Guidance)
javascriptconst generateBeatDraft = async (beat, storyContext, previousBeats) => {
  const prompt = `You are a storytelling expert helping someone write a beat in their story.

Structure: ${storyContext.structure.selected.name}
Current Beat: ${beat.name} (${beat.stage} of ${storyContext.structure.selected.totalBeats})
Beat Description: ${beat.desc}
Emotion: ${beat.emotion}

Story Context:
- Type: ${storyContext.storyType.type.name}
- Character: ${storyContext.character.primary?.name}
- Audience: ${storyContext.audience.primary}

Previous Beats (for continuity):
${previousBeats.map(b => `${b.beatName}: ${b.userContent}`).join('\n')}

Guiding Questions for this beat:
${beat.guidance.questions.join('\n')}

Write a 2-4 sentence draft for this beat that:
1. Answers the guiding questions
2. Maintains continuity with previous beats
3. Uses concrete, vivid language
4. Fits the emotional tone: ${beat.emotion}
5. Is appropriate for the story type and audience

Return only the draft text, no explanation.`;

  const response = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514',
      max_tokens: 400,
      messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }]
    })
  });

  const data = await response.json();
  return data.content.find(c => c.type === 'text')?.text.trim();
};
7.3 AI Outline Generation (Light Guidance)
javascriptconst generateStructureOutline = async (structure, storyContext) => {
  const prompt = `Generate a story outline using the ${structure.name} structure.

Story Context:
- Type: ${storyContext.storyType.type.name}
- Character: ${storyContext.character.primary?.name}
- Audience: ${storyContext.audience.primary}
- Purpose: ${storyContext.purpose}
- Conflict: ${storyContext.conflict?.central}

Structure: ${structure.name}
Key Beats: ${structure.beats.map(b => b.name).join(', ')}

Create a custom outline with ${structure.beats.length} beats. For each beat:
1. Use the beat name from the structure
2. Write a 1-2 sentence suggestion specific to their story
3. Indicate approximate duration as percentage

Return JSON array:
[
  {
    "beatName": "Beat name",
    "suggestion": "Specific suggestion for their story",
    "duration": "20%"
  }
]`;

  const response = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514',
      max_tokens: 2000,
      messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }]
    })
  });

  const data = await response.json();
  const textContent = data.content.find(c => c.type === 'text')?.text || '[]';
  const cleaned = textContent.replace(/```json\n?|```\n?/g, '').trim();
  return JSON.parse(cleaned);
};
8. Success Metrics
8.1 Primary Metrics

Usage rate: 85%+ of users select a structure
Completion rate by guidance level:

Deep Guidance: 70%+ complete all beats
Light Guidance: 85%+ accept AI outline
Quick Mode: 90%+ accept AI recommendation


Structure distribution: Track which structures are most popular

Expected: Man In A Hole (30%), Three-Act (25%), Hero's Journey (20%), Others (25%)


AI acceptance: 65%+ accept AI recommendations/drafts with minimal editing

8.2 Secondary Metrics

Guidance level choice (Comprehensive Mode):

Deep: 40%
Light: 60%


Time spent per guidance level:

Deep: 20-30 minutes average
Light: 8-12 minutes average


Beat completion patterns: Which beats take longest? Which are skipped?
AI draft usage: 60%+ request AI draft for at least one beat

8.3 Quality Metrics

Beat word count: Average 50-150 words per beat
Structure-story alignment: Do selected structures make sense for story types?
User satisfaction: "Does this structure help organize your story?" >4/5
Retention: 90%+ keep selected structure through completion

