## 9. Dependencies

### 9.1 Technical Dependencies
- **React Context API**: Story state management
- **Anthropic Claude API**: Structure recommendations, beat drafts, outline generation
- **Supabase Client**: Saving structure data, auto-save
- **Tailwind CSS**: Styling
- **React Router**: Navigation between beats
- **Recharts or similar** (optional): Emotional arc diagrams

### 9.2 Feature Dependencies

**Must be completed first**:
- âœ… Mode Selection (determines Quick vs. Comprehensive features)
- âœ… Story Type Selection (informs structure recommendations)
- âœ… Audience Questions (helps AI recommend appropriate structures)

**Optional but enhances**:
- ğŸ”„ Character/Archetype Builder (archetypes can inform structure choice and beat development)
- ğŸ”„ Moral Conflict Framework (moral conflicts can integrate into beats)

**Depends on Structure Selector**:
- â­ï¸ Scene Development Tool (scenes are built based on structure beats)
- â­ï¸ Visual Story Map (visualizes the selected structure)
- â­ï¸ Full Story Draft (uses structure as backbone)

### 9.3 Data Dependencies
- **Complete structures library**: All 18+ structures with full beat definitions
- **Story context**: Story type, audience, character for AI recommendations
- **Examples database**: Real-world examples for each structure and beat

## 10. User Acceptance Criteria

### 10.1 Acceptance Tests

**Test 1: Quick Mode - Auto Structure**
- âœ… User in Quick Mode enters structure selector
- âœ… AI automatically recommends structure based on story type
- âœ… Shows simple 3-beat outline
- âœ… User can accept or choose from 3 alternatives
- âœ… Selection saves and advances to next step

**Test 2: Comprehensive Mode - Deep Guidance**
- âœ… User chooses "Deep Guidance"
- âœ… Sees 5 curated structures with detailed info
- âœ… Clicks "Learn More" on Hero's Journey
- âœ… Modal shows full structure with all 12 beats
- âœ… User selects Hero's Journey
- âœ… Enters beat-by-beat editor
- âœ… Beat 1 displays with questions, examples, guidance
- âœ… User clicks "Generate AI Draft"
- âœ… AI generates 2-3 sentence draft
- âœ… User edits draft, saves, continues to Beat 2
- âœ… Progress bar shows 1/12 complete
- âœ… User completes all 12 beats
- âœ… All beats save to database

**Test 3: Comprehensive Mode - Light Guidance**
- âœ… User chooses "Light Guidance"
- âœ… Sees 15+ structures with brief descriptions
- âœ… Selects "Rags to Riches"
- âœ… AI generates custom 5-beat outline
- âœ… Each beat has specific suggestion for user's story
- âœ… User reviews outline
- âœ… Can edit beat suggestions inline
- âœ… Saves outline and continues

**Test 4: AI Structure Recommendation**
- âœ… User clicks "Get AI Recommendation"
- âœ… AI analyzes story context
- âœ… Recommends structure with confidence level
- âœ… Explains reasoning (2-3 sentences)
- âœ… Shows 2 alternative options
- âœ… User can accept recommendation or browse manually

**Test 5: Beat Progress & Auto-Save**
- âœ… User enters beat-by-beat editor
- âœ… Completes Beat 1
- âœ… Progress bar updates: 1/12 (8%)
- âœ… Auto-save occurs after 30 seconds
- âœ… Visual indicator shows "Saved"
- âœ… User closes browser mid-beat
- âœ… Returns later, work is preserved
- âœ… Can continue from where they left off

**Test 6: Guidance Questions & Examples**
- âœ… Each beat shows 3-5 guiding questions
- âœ… Questions are specific to the beat
- âœ… Examples section shows real-world instances
- âœ… Examples relevant to story type when possible
- âœ… "Tips" section provides additional guidance
- âœ… User can toggle examples on/off

**Test 7: Structure-Archetype Integration**
- âœ… User has selected "Warrior" archetype
- âœ… User selects "Hero's Journey" structure
- âœ… AI beat drafts incorporate Warrior qualities
- âœ… Guidance suggests Warrior-appropriate actions
- âœ… Examples reference similar Warrior journeys

**Test 8: Mobile Responsiveness**
- âœ… Structure grid displays 1 column on mobile
- âœ… Beat editor is full-screen on mobile
- âœ… Sidebar collapses to hamburger menu
- âœ… Progress bar remains visible at top
- âœ… All touch interactions work smoothly
- âœ… Text remains readable at mobile sizes

### 10.2 Edge Cases

**Incomplete Beat Content**:
- âœ… User tries to skip beat without content
- âœ… Warning: "This beat is empty. Skip anyway?"
- âœ… User can confirm skip or go back to complete

**Very Long Beat Content**:
- âœ… User writes 500+ word beat
- âœ… Character counter shows current count
- âœ… Gentle suggestion: "Beats work best at 50-150 words. Consider condensing."
- âœ… No hard limit, allows saving

**API Failure During Beat Generation**:
- âœ… AI service fails or times out
- âœ… Error message: "Couldn't generate draft. Please write manually or try again."
- âœ… Retry button available
- âœ… Beat editor remains functional for manual writing

**Switching Structures Mid-Process**:
- âœ… User has completed 5 beats of Hero's Journey
- âœ… User wants to switch to Man In A Hole
- âœ… Warning dialog: "You'll lose progress on current structure. Continue?"
- âœ… User can cancel or proceed
- âœ… If proceed, old beats are archived, new structure starts fresh

**No Story Context Available**:
- âœ… User somehow reaches structure selector without prior steps
- âœ… AI recommendations use generic prompts
- âœ… Encourages completing story type and audience first
- âœ… Manual selection still works fully

**Beat Navigation**:
- âœ… User can jump between beats using sidebar
- âœ… Incomplete beats show hollow circle
- âœ… Completed beats show filled checkmark
- âœ… Current beat is highlighted
- âœ… Can revisit and edit previous beats

## 11. Open Questions & Risks

### 11.1 Open Questions

1. **Should we allow custom structure creation?**
   - Pro: Ultimate flexibility for advanced users
   - Con: Loses framework benefits, hard to guide
   - **Recommendation**: No for MVP, consider for Phase 2

2. **Should beats be reorderable?**
   - Some structures are sequential, others flexible
   - **Recommendation**: Lock order for sequential structures, allow flexibility for others

3. **How to handle very long stories?**
   - 12-beat Hero's Journey for a novel = lots of content
   - **Recommendation**: Allow beat expansion (sub-beats) in Phase 2

4. **Should we show structure recommendations from other users?**
   - "85% of business pitches use Three-Act Structure"
   - **Recommendation**: Test in Phase 2 after gathering data

5. **Multi-structure stories?**
   - Some stories use multiple structures for different parts
   - **Recommendation**: MVP = single structure, Phase 2 = nested structures

### 11.2 Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Probability | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-------------|------------|
| Users overwhelmed by structure complexity | High | Medium | Clear guidance levels, AI recommendations, examples |
| Structure feels too restrictive | Medium | Medium | Emphasize as guide not formula, allow skipping beats |
| Deep Guidance too time-consuming | Medium | Medium | Auto-save, clear progress indicators, ability to pause |
| AI beat drafts are generic | High | Low | Context-aware prompts, user editing always available |
| Users don't complete all beats | Medium | High | Show progress, celebrate milestones, allow partial completion |
| Structure-story mismatch | High | Low | AI recommendations, detailed "best for" guidance |

### 11.3 Technical Risks

**Auto-Save Conflicts**:
- Risk: User edits on multiple devices, conflicting saves
- Mitigation: Last-write-wins with conflict detection, show warning

**AI Cost for Beat Drafts**:
- Risk: 12 beats Ã— many users = high API costs
- Mitigation: Optional feature, caching common patterns, smart prompting

**Performance with Large Beat Content**:
- Risk: Rich text editor slows with long beats
- Mitigation: Text area instead of rich editor, pagination for very long content

## 12. Implementation Notes

### 12.1 Vibe Coding Approach

This feature can be built in **5-6 development sessions**:

**Session 1: Guidance Level Selection & Structure Grid** (120 min)
```
Prompt to Claude:
"Build the Structure Selector for Storyteller Tactics.

Requirements:
GUIDANCE LEVEL (Comprehensive Mode only):
- Two cards: Deep Guidance vs. Light Guidance
- Clear value propositions for each
- AI recommendation option

STRUCTURE GRID:
- Display structure cards in responsive grid
- Each card shows: icon, name, short desc, difficulty, time, best for
- Emotional arc mini-graph
- Filter by arc type (Rise, Fall, Cycle, Complex, Template)
- "Learn More" opens detail modal

Structures data: [provide 5 Deep Guidance structures]
Use Tailwind, purple theme.
"
```

**Session 2: Structure Detail Modal & AI Recommendation** (120 min)
```
Prompt to Claude:
"Build Structure Detail Modal and AI Recommendation.

Requirements:
MODAL:
